rs-learn rlib bridge RECIPE (for a build-cycle session; loop-out-of-reach due to linkage risk). rs-learn (crates/wasm, crate-type cdylib+rlib) exposes: pub dispatch::dispatch_json<B:KvBackend>(&mut LearnSession<B>, raw:&[u8])->Vec<u8>; pub dispatch::LearnSession::new(kv); pub graph::host_kv_backend::HostKv (the wasm KvBackend over host imports). Its host imports (host_kv_get/put/query, host_vec_search, host_log, host_now_ms) are the SAME names rs-plugkit's wrapper already provides, so linking adds NO new imports. BRIDGE STEPS: (1) add rs-learn as git rlib dep in rs-plugkit [target.wasm32.dependencies]; (2) in wasm_dispatch.rs dispatch table, route learn-* verbs (insert_edge/query_at/invalidate_edge/contradict/init_instant/feedback/apply_adapter/reset_adapter/record_loss/consolidate/ewc_penalty/init_router/route/record_outcome/init_attention/attend) to a helper that calls rs_learn::dispatch::dispatch_json(&mut LearnSession::new(HostKv), body_bytes); (3) add the learn-* verbs to the gm spool ABI + AGENTS.md. LINKAGE RISK (why local build needed first): both crates are large wasm cdylibs each registering getrandom-custom + a panic handler + candle/tokenizers — linking both into one wasm may collide on those globals or pull duplicate/incompatible candle, a build-green-but-runtime-broken failure. REQUIRED: local cargo build --release --target wasm32-wasip1 --features wasm + dispatch a learn-* verb as a runtime smoke test before pushing. Only then is rs-learn's temporal graph + instant-LoRA + EWC + FastGRNN router + attention live as agent verbs.